cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the deployment scenarios and optimization of network parameters for uplink massive Machine-Type Communications (MTC) in LTE, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the effect of packet bundling on reducing overhead and resource waste, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of aggregators and the tradeoff between access congestion and resource starvation is a topic of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions monitoring applications, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
